mysql_db:
Please do not ask meta questions in the chat!
A meta question is a question that implies other questions, for example:

Can I ask a question?
Is there anyone who understands N?
And did anyone here take a course from Yandex on the cursor? There is a text analysis question ...
Guys, there is a question for% framework_name%
“It’s clear, but what’s wrong with these questions and why shouldn’t I ask them?”

- They are wasting time! And yours, and other people who are trying to help you! You try to be polite, without going straight to your problem, as people do in person. But chat is completely different. People type much slower than they say. Instead of being polite, you force the other person to wait while you formulate the question, which leads to a loss of performance.

The same applies to such messages: “Hello”, “Hello. Are you here? ”,“ Have a minute? ”,“ Ping. ” Just ask a question!

In addition, when you ask a question immediately, the possibility of asynchronous interaction opens up. If the other person is unavailable, and you leave before he returns, he can still answer the question, instead of looking at your “Hello” and thinking about what happened.
